

## 📝 Day 1 Summary

Day 1 focused on building a GitHub repository data ingestion pipeline for an AI Agent system. The project used Python to download repository documentation from GitHub as a ZIP archive, extract markdown files (`.md`, `.mdx`), and parse structured metadata using frontmatter. Libraries such as `requests`, `zipfile`, `io`, and `python-frontmatter` were used to efficiently fetch, process, and organize documentation data into a structured format. This step prepares repository documentation for future AI tasks such as chunking, indexing, semantic search, retrieval systems, and conversational AI agents.

